OL,5,Cwide web
OL,7,FAlthough it could have earned him a
OL,8,Ffortune had he patented it, Sir Tim
OL,9,FBerners-Lee gave his invention away
OL,10,Ffor free. The ability for everybody to
OL,11,Fhave access to the vast network of
OL,12,Finformation offered on the web was
OL,13,Fvery important to him. He conceived
OL,14,Fthe web as a means of connecting ideas
OL,15,Frather than making money.
OL,17,FOf course, today the web is the source
OL,18,Fof revenue for some of the world's
OL,19,Frichest people, including Jeff Bezos,
OL,20,FElon Musk and Mark Zuckerberg.
